  "explanationRemotePair": "{chainDesc} all hold only {a} and {b}, and each sees the next, so their values alternate along the chain. The two ends sit an odd number of steps apart, so one is {a} and the other is {b} — meaning any cell seeing both ends can have BOTH {a} and {b} removed.",
